  <prompt>Update `src/server/shared/Spaarke.Core/Cache/DistributedCacheExtensions.cs` — change hardcoded `"sdap"` key prefix to `"spaarke"` (FR-07). Where helper is still used outside the BFF wrapper boundary (shared lib consumers), keep the existing public API contract so consumers don't break. Internal BFF call sites will migrate to `ITenantCache` in tasks 010–017.</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke .NET developer; preserve public API; targeted internal change.</role>
  <goal>`CreateKey()` produces `spaarke:{category}:{id}:v{version}` (or whatever the existing helper shape is — preserve shape, swap prefix). All Spaarke.Core consumers compile; existing tests pass.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>FR-07 mandates the `sdap:` → `spaarke:` switch. The helper is shared, so we change it once here; the BFF-only `ITenantCache` wrapper supersedes it for new code and the migration tasks (010+).</background>
